- how you knew this person
- what he/she usually talks about
- explain how you felt about him/her

I’d like to talk about a friend of mine who really enjoys talking, and that is my best friend Minh.

I first met him about five years ago when I started high school. We were in the same class, and he sat next to me. He was actually the first person to talk to me, which made me feel much more comfortable on my first day.

In terms of personality, Minh is very outgoing and sociable. He’s the kind of person who can easily start a conversation with anyone. He’s also quite talkative and has a great sense of humor, so he often tells jokes or shares interesting stories to make people laugh. He usually talks about daily life, social media trends, or even random things he finds online.

For me, he’s like a “walking news channel” because he always keeps me updated with what’s going on. What I like most about him is that, even though he talks a lot, he is also a good listener and always gives helpful advice when I need it.

Of course, there are times when he can be a bit distracting, especially when I need to focus on something important. But overall, I really enjoy spending time with him, and I feel lucky to have such a fun and supportive friend.
